    <h3>Projects</h3>
    <p><a href="">nterrafranca.com</a><br> This site you are looking at is a simple Sinatra application built with very little framework "magic". No Foundation, no Bootstrap. I wanted to get back to the nitty-gritty and write good old fashioned Ruby, JavaScript, HTML and CSS. With a little help from PostgreSql and a lightweight email solution called Pony, this app will continue growing iteratively develop new features and content.<a href=""> View Code</a></p>

    <p><a href="http://uberchef.herokuapp.com" target="_blank"> UberChef</a><br>This MVP stage Rail application allows the user to connect with professional chefs for any number of culinary endeavors. After the user posts an event, chefs can then browse, search for and bid on events of their choice. The app also features a user-to-user messaging feature to facilitate direct communication for detailed bid negotiation. This app was prototyped while attending Launch Academy and continues to be a sandbox for new ideas and features.<a href="https://github.com/NickTerrafranca/uberchef" target="_blank"> View Code</a></p>

    <p><a href="http://fizzbuzzapp.herokuapp.com" target="_blank">FizzBuzz</a><br>This is a beer brewery review site worked while attending Launch Academy. As part of a small development team, I worked on the user authentication, schema design, Admin name-spacing and front-end design. This Ruby on Rail application made use of a brewery data API and gems like Devise, CarrierWave, ActionMailer and Bootstrap. The development of this app was fully test driven.<a href="https://github.com/LaunchAcademy/fizz_buzz" target="_blank"> View Code</a></p>
